# ============================================
# Frontend Environment Configuration
# ============================================

# IMPORTANT: How to use this file:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Uncomment the appropriate configuration based on your setup
# 3. DO NOT commit .env.local to git

# ============================================
# Option 1: LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (without ngrok)
# ============================================
# Use this configuration when running the backend locally on http://localhost:8000
# The Vite proxy will automatically forward /api requests to http://localhost:8000
# 
# Leave VITE_API_URL empty or commented out:
# VITE_API_URL=

# ============================================
# Option 2: PRODUCTION / REMOTE BACKEND (with ngrok)
# ============================================
# Use this configuration when backend is deployed remotely with ngrok
# Replace the URL with your actual ngrok URL
# 
# Example:
VITE_API_URL=https://historiographical-uninjuriously-doreatha.ngrok-free.dev

# ============================================
# Optional: JIRA Integration Settings
# ============================================
# IMPORTANT: JIRA configuration has fallback mechanism:
# Priority: localStorage > VITE environment variables > defaults
# 
# If not set via environment variables, you can configure in the app UI
# (Settings page) and it will be saved to localStorage
# 
# Configuration sources (in priority order):
# 1. localStorage (user saves via Settings UI)
# 2. VITE_JIRA_* environment variables (this file or Vercel env vars)
# 3. App will work without JIRA config (graceful degradation)
#
# Example for development:
# VITE_JIRA_URL=https://your-jira-instance.atlassian.net
# VITE_JIRA_EMAIL=your-email@example.com
# VITE_JIRA_API_TOKEN_1=your-api-token-for-local-dev
# VITE_JIRA_API_TOKEN_2=your-api-token-for-production

# For Vercel deployment, set these in Vercel dashboard:
# Settings â†’ Environment Variables
# - VITE_JIRA_URL
# - VITE_JIRA_EMAIL
# - VITE_JIRA_API_TOKEN_1
# - VITE_JIRA_API_TOKEN_2
